The 2 aspects of the game pitching and batting both are terrible. You have no fine control of pitches and no pitch selection as in curve, slider, sinker, or change up and batting there's no camera control so you're stuck batting at a terrible angle. To make matters worse you have a fraction of a second to swing or not once the pitcher throws. No time to see if the pitch is in the dirt or way outside. You just swing and hope which hits a most common foul ball. Wasted my money.

This is a very simple simulation of Major League Baseball. You bat. You throw. You make team selections. That's it. There are some minor trade options. This isnt a bad thing if you want that easy 'pick up and play' experience but it does lack depth. What really bothers me at the moment are the clunky animations (are frames missing?) and clunky AI (fielders making hard work of throwing simple balls to bases). The developers really should be doing a better job.

RBI 19 is unplayable unless you are devoted to baseball on your smartphone. The gameplay is solid while the controls are slippery. (Causes you to 'hang' pitches or hit grounders.) The biggest issue is the fact that you (and your opponent) can hit dozens of singles, but homeruns are few a far between. It's truly a deadball era simulator. If this game gets an update patch, this could be rectified and it'll be a strong 4/5 like previous entries.

I was excited to play this game, as the graphics looked very good, but the gameplay is quite atrocious. The frame rate is horrendous, making batting near impossible, and I'm using a Galaxy S9. And pitching is strangely simplistic: there's no pitch meter, and you can't place the ball where you want it . Instead of selecting a pitch type, you weirdly move the analog stick in one of four directions and then tap a button - that's it. And you can't change the camera angle either. Huge disappointment.
